news.title: China property stocks surge on fundraising support
news.para: The move will make it easier for developers to obtain fresh funding, analysts said, but reviving demand from homebuyers would remain challenging amid persisting COVID-19 curbs that have triggered rare street protests across many Chinese cities.

news.title: Mortgage approvals in Britain hit lowest since June 2020
news.para: Britain's housing market is showing clear signs of slowing, with various gauges of house prices now showing cooling inflation after rapid growth during the pandemic.

news.title: Shimao Group Holdings to raise funds as Beijing lifts equity sales ban
news.para: Shimao's fundraising target will not exceed 30% of the current capital base, it said. Based on the developer's market value of 11.3 billion yuan ($1.58 billion) on Wednesday the deal size could be up to $474 million.

news.title: Take action against erring builders in Bihar: DGP
news.para: “As per the direction of the high court, the FIR should be registered against the builders in such cases in which houses/flats have not been made available to the customers by the builders after taking money from them,” he said.

news.title: IFC partially exits Puravankara's Bengaluru project
news.para: The exit — from 1.4 million square feet plotted development project spread over 60 acres — was at an internal rate of return of 20%. The project is at an advanced stage of completion with 80% of the houses sold out. IFC had invested Rs 157 crore in the project over the last two years.

news.title: Illegal hoardings to prove costly for property owners in Pune
news.para: The PMC has decided to recover advertisings charges via property tax from owners for allowing illegal hoardings on their promises. They hope to earn around Rs125 crore as additional tax from such hoardings.

news.title: Auction of lapsed sand mining leases in Rajasthan in December
news.para: While three leases in Jalore, Sayala and Kotri were closed four months ago, the tenure of the other three including Nath Dwara, Deoli and Raj Samand will expire in February.

news.title: Google pics show shrinking forest, Uttarakhand HC stays construction in hamlet
news.para: The order was issued on November 23 by a division bench of chief justice Vipin Sanghi and justice RC Khulbe. It said no construction activities in Jilling Estate would be carried out till December 15.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to sanction housing for poor in their own plots: Minister
news.para: Ramesh — as part of his tour in north Andhra districts — visited Jagananna layout colonies in Anakapalli, Visakhapatnam, and Vizianagaram districts on Tuesday.

news.title: HSVP puts its land up for auction, finds 13 acres occupied by Gurugram civic body
news.para: The encroachment came to light when HSVP, which is reeling from a financial crisis and has been monetising its assets to raise funds, listed some of its land for auction.

news.title: Use only recycled water for construction in New Town Kolkata: NKDA
news.para: From now on, construction agencies will only have to use recycled water, to be supplied by the New Town Kolkata Development Authority (NKDA), at construction sites in the township.

news.title: SC gives bail to Popular Builders' owner in two land grabbing cases
news.para: ​While granting him bail, the court externed him from Gujarat and ordered him to keep city police posted about his location by activating his mobile GPS device.

news.title: Maharashtra: Now, apply online to make changes in 7/12 extracts
news.para: The state settlement commissioner’s office has developed a software to enable citizens to apply for the changes online by registering on the public data entry portal.

news.title: 'Model code' on pollution could be way out of winter ban: HSPCB chief to realtors
news.para: Construction stops under measures prescribed by the graded response action plan (GRAP) to bring down air pollution levels in Delhi-NCR, which typically peak at the onset of winter due to farm fires and climatic causes.

news.title: Wants to regulate realty sector without hampering development: H-RERA, chairman
news.para: "Our intention has always been to make developers in Gurugram region to make them compliant with RERA law and not penalise them," K K Khandelwal said, adding that very small amount of penalities have been imposed by the authority in some cases.
